This is so simple and yet so wonderful! I serve it regularly over "Farina pudding with fresh fruit" (in place of the fruit suggeswted of course.) It also works well with nectarines, apricots, prunes, and plums. I want to try it with fresh figs next.

Rating: 4
Served this for desert after a BBQ dinner--outstanding. I added 1.5 ounces of Frangelico to this. Served in crepes. Sprinkled all with sliced almonds. Then served a heaping bowl of whipped cream (cream, 2 tablespoons brown sugar, 1.5 ounces of Frangelico) and let everyone spoon on their own dollops of cream. Outstanding and a great hit!

